Configuration files that are to be edited for sure while installing a hadoop cluster:
   >Core-site.xml
   >HDFS-site.xml
   >YARN-site.xml
   >xml
   Hadoop comes up with default configurations in *-default.xml. For example: hdfs-default.xml, yarn-default.xml, etc.
   • Default configurations are overridden in *-site.xml. For example: hdfs-site.xml, yarn-site.xml, etc
  configurations to be checked:
   • dfs.replication.max   • dfs.heartbeat.interval • dfs.namenode.checkpoint.check.period
   • dfs.hosts • dfs.hosts.exclude  • dfs.namenode.checkpoint.edits.dir
  • dfs.namenode.checkpoint.txns   • dfs.bytes-per-checksum• dfs.namenode.replication.min
   • dfs.namenode.checkpoint.max-retries • dfs.blocksize• dfs.namenode.checkpoint.dir • dfs.namenode.checkpoint.period 
